// Interacting With The Browser
// 1. Changing Styles: Write a function that changes the color of the text in a paragraph when a button
// is clicked.
// 2. Form Validation: Create a form and write a script that validates the input fields when the form is
// submitted.
// 3. DOM Manipulation: Write a script that adds a new item to a list when a button is clicked.
// 4. Event Handling: Write a script that logs a message to the console when a mouseover event
// occurs on an image.
// 5. Window Object: Write a script that uses the window.location object to redirect the user to
// another webpage.
// 6. Timer: Write a script that starts a timer and updates the text content of an element with the
// current time left every second.
// 7. Local Storage: Write a script that stores a user’s name in local storage and retrieves it when the
// page is reloaded.
// 8. AJAX Request: Write a script that fetches data from an API and displays it on the webpage.
// 9. Error Handling: Write a script that handles errors when an image fails to load.
// 10. User Interaction: Write a script that changes the background color of the webpage based on the
// user’s keyboard input.